The Proposal: -

The decision regarding imparting education to the students of Dhangar community belonging to nomadic tribe-C category in reputed English medium residential schools in the cities has been taken vide Reference No. 1 is mentioned here. The decision of the Government of 4/9/2019 to increase the number of students under the scheme from 5500 per annum to 10000 per annum has been taken subject to additional criteria. 2 is mentioned here. Approval has been granted under the Government Decision of 5.3.2024. The Director, Directorate of Other Backward Bahujan Welfare, M.R., Pune has issued a notification in this regard at No. Under the letter mentioned in 4 and 5, a proposal has been submitted to the Government along with the prescribed forms (Total score obtained by the school for the year 2024-25 -61) to select Siddhivinayak English School, Limbaganesh, T.G. Beed, a school run by Sri Krishna Multipurpose Service Foundation, Beed, under the "Nominated School" scheme and approve the admission of students from the Dhangar community to this school for the academic year 2024-25. Accordingly, under the scheme of "Educating students of Dhangar community of Nomadic Tribes-C category in reputed English medium residential schools in cities *," the Government was contemplating to approve the admission of 100 students of Dhangar community of Nomadic Tribes-C category for the academic year 2011, subject to the terms and conditions of the relevant Government decision, by selecting the Sri Krishna Multi-Purpose Service Institute, Sidhivinayak English School, Limbaganesh, T.G. Beed, a school run by Beed.
The Government's Decisions:

Sri Krishna Multi-Purpose Charitable Trust, Beed operates under the scheme of "Educating students of Dhangar community belonging to Nomadic Tribes-C category in reputed English medium residential schools in cities."

The selection of Siddhivinayak English School, Limbaganesh, T.G. Beed and admission of 100 students from the Dhangar community belonging to the nomadic tribe-C category for the academic year 2024-25 as mentioned in the table below is being approved by the Government subject to the terms and conditions in the relevant Government Decision.

The following terms and conditions should be adhered to while admission to the designated school: - 1) The Government Decision with respect to the institution / school concerned, the criteria in the date 4/9/2019 as well as the Government Decision, d. Additional criteria, terms, and conditions in the 5/3/2024 will need to be met.

The Assistant Director, Other Backward Classes Bahujan Kalyan concerned shall take further appropriate action regarding the allotment of students by ensuring that the norms and conditions of the respective Government decision are met by the respective institution / school.

The school should be inspected in accordance with the National Register of Residential Schools scheme and all students enrolled in the school should be registered by verifying their Aadhaar card. Subsequently, the government decision, by verifying the number of beneficiary students present in person and the number of resident students in person, was passed. 04/09/2019 and Government Decisions, d. The detailed report as per the terms and conditions in the 5/4/2024 should be submitted to the Government through the Director, Directorate of Other Backward Bahujan Welfare, Pune for disbursement of funds with the approval of the Regional Deputy Director, Other Backward Bahujan Welfare (Regional) Department.

2- The Assistant Director, Other Backward Classes Bahujan Kalyan concerned shall ensure that the institution is ready to provide all the facilities mentioned in the proposal submitted to the Government by the institution / school concerned regarding student approval under the scheme and such agreement shall be entered into with the institution.

4) The institution / school is not expected to start a separate batch / class for a student from Dhangar community belonging to nomadic tribe-C category, it will be mandatory to educate the students enrolled under the scheme along with other students in the regular batch / class that is going on in the school. If it is found that a separate unit / class has been started for the student, action will be taken to register a case against the institution and the recognition of the school will be cancelled immediately.
5) It is mandatory to appoint a female superintendent as a caretaker in the girls' hostel admitted to the institute. If this is found to be not met, the school will be de-recognised.

6) The Assistant Director, Other Backward Classes Bahujan Kalyan of the concerned district shall take care of the admission of students belonging to the Dhangar community belonging to the nomadic tribe-C category in the schools approved by the government under the scheme and within the limit of the number of students sanctioned for the respective school.
7) As per the basic provision of the scheme, the benefit of the scheme should be given only to the children whose annual family income is limited to Rs.

8) The Assistant Director, Other Backward Bahujan Welfare of the concerned district should immediately complete the process of student admission by giving preference to the nearest school and the selected schools in the respective project while admitting the students.

Also, publish a list of students who have not been selected. These students should be admitted to the selected school in the project.

(10) The Directors / Principals of the nominated schools selected under the scheme along with the Assistant Director, Other Backward Classes Bahujan Kalyan of the concerned district shall hold meetings in the first and second semester of the academic year to review the academic progress of the admitted students and the facilities provided to them.

(11) After the school is selected under the nominated scheme, the Assistant Director of the concerned district, Other Backward Bahujan Welfare, on two occasions in the first semester and on two times in the second semester, should suddenly visit the nominated schools in person and submit a report to the government through the Director, Directorate of Other Backward Bahujan Welfare, Pune, regarding all the aspects of the school, including the environment, facilities provided to the students, medication, educational quality, nutrition, etc.

(12) Subject to reference, the Government Decision dated 4/9/2019 and the Government Decision, d. Strictly follow the prescribed provisions in the 5/3/2024. Schools that do not comply with these provisions will be de-recognised.
